    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>NORTH KOREAN BUSINESS RISKS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Samuel Len</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Len, Samuel</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>South Korea will propose agreements designed to minimize risks by businesses seeking to enter North Korean markets (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>South Korea's government plans to propose that Pyongyang sign a set of agreements to minimize risks faced by businesses seeking to enter North Korea, according to Lee Ki Ho, the top economic adviser to South Korea's president. Through the proposed agreement, the South Korean government seeks to secure a legal framework to protect investments in the North, while preventing double taxation, and to develop a concerted plan to deal with labor disputes.</p>
        <p>Samuel Len (NYT)</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
